de.wwu.muggl.vm
Class Frame

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.vm.Frame
Direct Known Subclasses:
SymbolicFrame
public class Frame
extends java.lang.Object

A frame is the element used in virtual machines to represent a methods during execution. It therefore holds a reference to the specific methods, as well as runtime specific information as the local variables, the pc etc.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-07-1^5
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

returnFromMethod

public void returnFromMethod()
Clears the operand stack and sets this frame inactive. This will result in control given back to the invoking frame (or there execution to end, if there was no invoking frame).

returnFromMethod

public void returnFromMethod(java.lang.Object value)
Pushes a returned object onto the stack of the invoking frame, or if there was none onto the virtual machines stack and sets the frame inactive. Clears this frames' operand stack afterwards.

Parameters:
value - The value returned from the method.
